==English==
===Pronunciation===
*''US'': too͞'nə, /ˈtuːnə/, /"tu:n@/
*''British'', ''Aus'': tyoo͞'nə, /ˈtjuːnə/, /"tju:n@/

===Etymology===
American Spanish alteration of the Spanish ''[[atún]],'' modified from the Arabic ''tūn,'' from the Latin ''[[thunnus]],'' from the Greek ''thynnos.''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''tuna''' (''plural'' tuna or [[tunas]])

# any of several species of [[fish]], of the genus ''[[Thunnus]]'', in the family ''[[Scombridae]]''.
# the [[edible]] [[flesh]] of the tuna
# a type of [[cactus]] native to Mexico
# the [[fruit]] of the cactus

==== Synonyms ====
*[[tuna fish]] (US 1,2)

